WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.240 --> 00:00:10.120
By the summer of 1944.
the terror and tyranny

2
00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:13.280
of the Nazi Third Reich
shrouds most of Europe.

3
00:00:13.440 --> 00:00:16.720
Occupied countries
resist as they can.

4
00:00:16.880 --> 00:00:19.960
But with the advance of
Soviet forces in the east.

5
00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:23.240
and the success of the Normandy
invasion in the west.

6
00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:25.120
two of the world's great cities

7
00:00:25.280 --> 00:00:28.360
organize in force and fight back.

8
00:00:28.520 --> 00:00:31.360
Even in the place of
greatest horror.

9
00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:33.520
there is resistance.

10
00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:37.520
All wars change the world.

11
00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:39.400
but none of them
changed the world

12
00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:41.480
like the Second World War did.

13
00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:44.840
Japan's on the march.
Germany's on the march.

14
00:00:46.040 --> 00:00:49.040
No one can imagine the nightmare
they're about to unleash.

15
00:00:49.200 --> 00:00:52.000
The most destructive
war in human history.

16
00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:55.000
Suddenly. the world
is turned upside down

17
00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:57.320
and all hell is let loose.

18
00:00:58.520 --> 00:01:02.040
The West is stunned by
the speed of the advance.

19
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.600
You get the Allies
led by the big three:

20
00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:07.960
Roosevelt. Churchill. Stalin.

21
00:01:08.120 --> 00:01:10.040
Men who are dealing with

22
00:01:10.200 --> 00:01:13.000
immensely
complicated questions.

23
00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:17.040
It's the biggest military
operation of human history.

24
00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:19.040
The Allies have to come together.

25
00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:21.160
not just militarily.
but industrial scale.

26
00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:23.520
It's a global perspective.

27
00:01:23.680 --> 00:01:25.120
They have to fight in
every climate

28
00:01:25.280 --> 00:01:28.160
from the Arctic to the jungles
of the Pacific.

29
00:01:28.320 --> 00:01:30.760
to the deserts of Africa

30
00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:32.720
and the depths of the ocean.

31
00:01:34.760 --> 00:01:37.360
But there was no
certainty of victory.

32
00:01:37.520 --> 00:01:40.320
It was going to be
a horrific bloodbath.

33
00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:42.400
We see humans at
their absolute worst.

34
00:01:42.560 --> 00:01:44.520
how they treat other human beings.

35
00:01:44.680 --> 00:01:46.800
and we see them at their
absolute best.

36
00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:49.000
willing to give their lives
that others might live.

37
00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:50.960
World War II was a struggle

38
00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:53.960
in which there could be
one victor...

39
00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:55.680
...and one vanquished.

40
